properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 3:05AM CST until January 11 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Dodge City KS
properties.description:
* WHAT...Freezing rain and rain are expected to gradually change
to snow from northwest to southeast today and tonight. Total
snow accumulations up to 1 inch are forecast, with ice
accumulations of around one tenth of an inch. The best chance of
significant ice accumulations is across Pawnee, Rush, Pratt,
Kiowa and Stafford counties. Winds will gust as high as 50 mph
late this afternoon. Wind chills will drop below zero tonight.

* WHERE...Portions of central, south central and southwest
Kansas.

* WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 6 AM CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 6 AM CST SATURDAY
